definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  10-deoxysarpagine + H(+) + NADPH + O(2) -eq- H(2)O + NADP(+) + sarpagine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + NADPH + O(2) + phenylacetone -eq- benzyl acetate + H(2)O + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + lithocholate + NADPH + O(2) -eq- 6-beta-hydroxylithocholate + H(2)O + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  7alpha-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one + H(+) + NADPH + O(2) -eq- 7alpha,12alpha-dihydroxycholest-4-en-3-one + H(2)O + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  5beta-cholestane-3alpha,7alpha-diol + H(+) + NADPH + O(2) -eq- 5beta-cholestane-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-triol + H(2)O + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reactions -  taurochenodeoxycholate + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- taurohyocholate + NADP+ + H2O, and lithocholate + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- hyodeoxycholate + NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cholesterol + H(+) + NADPH + O(2) -eq- (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol + H(2)O + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (24R)-cholest-5-ene-3beta,24-diol + H(+) + NADPH + O(2) -eq- (24R)-7alpha,24-dihydroxycholesterol + H(2)O + NADP(+).

Catalysis of the reactions -  cholest-5-ene-3beta,25-diol + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- cholest-5-ene-3beta,7alpha,25-triol + NADP+ + H2O, and cholest-5-ene-3beta,27-diol + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- cholest-5-ene-3beta,7alpha,27-triol + NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + NADPH + O(2) + senecionine -eq- H(2)O + NADP(+) + senecionine N-oxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-alpha,beta-D-heptose-7-phosphate + ATP -eq- D-beta-D-heptose-1,7-bisphosphate + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-beta-D-heptose-1-phosphate + ATP -eq- ADP-D-glycero-D-manno-heptose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cob(I)alamin + hydrogen cyanide + NADP(+) -eq- cyanocob(III)alamin + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (2R,3S)-catechin + NADP+ + H2O -eq- 2,3-trans-3,4-cis-leucocyanidin + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 1,4-benzoquinone + H(2)O + phenylacetyl-CoA -eq- 2 hydroquinone + phenylglyoxylyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-hydroxymethylfurfural + NAD(P)H + H+ -eq- 2,5-bis-hydroxymethylfuran + NAD(P)+.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA + H2O + acceptor -eq- (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha,24-tetrahydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reactions -  deoxycholate + FAD + H2O -eq- cholate + FADH2, and lithocholate + FAD + H2O -eq- chenodeoxycholate + FADH2.
Catalysis of the reactions -  2',4,4',6'-tetrahydroxychalcone + O2 -eq- aureusidin + H2O, and 2',3,4,4',6'-pentahydroxychalcone + 1|2 O2 -eq- aureusidin + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl phosphate + methylamine + thioredoxin disulfide -eq- N-methylglycine + phosphate + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl phosphate + trimethylamine + thioredoxin disulfide -eq- N,N,N-trimethylglycine + phosphate + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reduction of elemental sulfur or polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 e(-) + 2 H(+) + selenate -eq- H(2)O + selenite.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3,3',5'-triiodo-L-thyronine + iodide + A + H+ -eq- L-thyroxine + AH2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + myricetin -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + laricitrin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a 7-hydroxyisoflavone -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + a 7-methoxyisoflavone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + vitexin 2''-O-beta-L-rhamnoside -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 7-O-methylvitexin 2''-O-beta-L-rhamnoside.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + isoliquiritigenin -eq- 2'-O-methylisoliquiritigenin + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + kaempferol -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(+) + kaempferide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-threonine + fluoroacetaldehyde -eq- acetaldehyde + 4-fluoro-L-threonine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  stearoyl-CoA + malonyl-CoA + 2 NAD(P)H + 2 H+ -eq- icosanoyl-CoA + CO2 + 2 NAD(P)+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3 malonyl-CoA + 4-coumaroyl-CoA + NADPH + H+ -eq- 4 CoA + isoliquiritigenin + 3 CO2 + NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonyl-CoA + an anthocyanidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside -eq- CoA + an anthocyanidin 3-O-(6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside).
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonyl-CoA + pelargonidin 3-O-(6-caffeoyl-beta-D-glucoside) 5-O-beta-D-glucoside -eq- CoA + 4'''-demalonylsalvianin.

Catalysis of the reaction -  4-coumaroyl-CoA + a flavonol 3-O-[beta-D-glucosyl-(1--gt-2)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1--gt-2)-beta-D-glucoside] -eq- CoA + a flavonol 3-O-[6-(4-coumaroyl)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1--gt-2)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1--gt-2)-beta-D-glucoside].
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinyl-CoA + acetyl-CoA -eq- CoA + 3-oxoadipyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + deacetylcephalosporin C -eq- cephalosporin C + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholanoyl-CoA + propanoyl-CoA -eq- CoA + 3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-24-oxo-5beta-cholestanoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3 malonyl-CoA + benzoyl-CoA -eq- 4 CoA + 3,5-dihydroxybiphenyl + 4 CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-2,4-diaminobutyrate + acetyl-CoA -eq- N(4)-acetyl-L-2,4-diaminobutyrate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (Z)-hexadec-11-enoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + malonyl-[acyl-carrier protein] -eq- (Z)-3-oxooctadec-13-enoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + CO2 + [acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + malonyl-[acyl-carrier protein] -eq- acetoacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + CoA + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  octanoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + protein -eq- protein N6-(octanoyl)lysine + acyl-carrier protein.
Catalysis of the transfer of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue from UDP-glucose to a hydroxymethylcytosine residue in DNA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a beta-D-glucosyl residue from UDP-glucose to a hydroxymethylcytosine residue in DNA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a beta-D-glucosyl residue from UDP-glucose to a glucosylhydroxymethylcytosine residue in DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + 5-(D-galactosyloxy)-L-lysine-procollagen -eq- UDP + 1,2-D-glucosyl-5-D-(galactosyloxy)-L-lysine-procollagen.

Catalysis of the transfer of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue from sucrose to alternately the 6-position and the 3-position of the non-reducing terminal residue of an alpha-D-glucan, thus producing a glucan having alternating alpha-1,6- and alpha-1,3-linkages.

Catalysis of the transfer of the non-reducing terminal alpha-D-glucose residue from a 1,4-alpha-D-glucan to the 4-position of an alpha-D-glucan, thus bringing about the hydrolysis of oligosaccharides.
Catalysis of the transfer of a beta-D-glucosyl residue from UDP-glucose on to a glucose residue in xyloglucan, forming a beta-1,4-D-glucosyl-D-glucose linkage.
